name: New Normal
description: This work reflects society by only showing a piece of the image, where people often see the situation only in part, not seeing it as a whole. People wearing masks are interpreted as a sign of silence on the impact of propaganda that continues to be echoed by related parties. Where the things that continue to be echoed have become a new Big Other for the community. The mask here has transcended the need for clothing, it has been subjected to symbolic narratives and power relations between the superior and the inferior. However, there are always loopholes and paradoxes of the propaganda that can be resisted.
